From 052617057872b0829d77d51ad174e6c24b548e92 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 20:58:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(postprocess): add user-shader runtime (Phase 1, OpenGL)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements §3 + §6 of the CRT/post-process shader plan in the consuming
repo (Battleship docs/crt_shader_plan_2026-05-11.md), plus a working
OpenGL backend. Designed to be game-agnostic so other LUS ports (SoH,
2S2H, Starship) can adopt it unchanged.

Public surface additions on Fast::GfxRenderingAPI (all non-pure with
no-op defaults, so existing backends keep building):
  - SupportsPostProcess()       -> bool
  - CreatePostProcessProgram(src)
  - DestroyPostProcessProgram(id)
  - RunPostProcess(id, srcFb, dstFb, params)

Interpreter additions:
  - PostProcessChain helper owns a single sampleable output FBO,
    compiles + retains one fragment program, runs the fullscreen pass.
  - ComposeFinalFrame() factors the post-MSAA-resolve composition out
    of Run() and RunGuiOnly(); when the chain is active it forces the
    MSAA fast path to resolve to a texture (plan §3.1).
  - StartFrame() reconciles two CVars each frame
    (gPostProcessEnabled, gPostProcessShader) and compiles/unloads on
    transitions only.
  - PostProcessSourceLoader resolves shader names against the
    filesystem (./shaders/<name>.glsl) first, then the f3d.o2r archive
    (shaders/postprocess/<name>.glsl).

OpenGL backend:
  - Compiles a fixed pass-through vertex shader (NDC fullscreen
    triangle + FlipY uniform that picks between mGameFb invertY=true
    and mGameFbMsaaResolved invertY=false sources) linked against the
    user FS.
  - Runs the pass with scissor/blend/depth disabled, restores
    mOpenglVbo + mOpenglVao bindings so the regular DrawTriangles
    path is unaffected.

Bundled builtin: shaders/postprocess/scanlines.glsl -- original MIT
work in this repo, demonstrates the standard uniform schema
(Source / SourceSize / OutputSize / InputSize / FrameCount /
FrameDirection). Users can drop their own GLSL files under
./shaders/<name>.glsl at install time.

Out of scope for this commit (follow-ups):
  - D3D11 + Metal backend implementations (default no-op overrides
    keep them building; SupportsPostProcess() = false at runtime).
  - SPIRV-Cross + glslang transpiler glue (the per-backend
    PostProcessSource.{hlsl,msl} fields are reserved for it).
  - .glslp / .slangp multi-pass preset support.

Implemented from the libretro/Mednafen public shader-uniform spec.
No code copied from RetroArch or any GPL-licensed shader runtime.

